                <h3 class="subsection-title">Step 1: Select Your Stock</h3>
                <p>Choose from the 7 Bro Billionaire stocks: Nvidia, Tesla, Palantir, Microsoft, Meta, Amazon, or Apple. Each has unique risk-return profiles.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">Step 2: Enter Investment Amount</h3>
                <p>Input how much you invested (or plan to invest). Works for any amount from ₹1,000 to ₹10 crore+.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">Step 3: Choose Currency</h3>
                <p>Select USD or INR. For INR, the calculator automatically adjusts for USD-INR exchange rate movements over your holding period.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">Step 4: Select Dates</h3>
                <p>Choose your purchase date (when you bought or plan to buy) and sell date (when you sold or current date). The calculator uses actual historical prices.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">Step 5: Enable Dividend Reinvestment (Optional)</h3>
                <p>If you're calculating returns for Apple or Microsoft, check this box to include quarterly dividend reinvestment. This significantly boosts long-term returns.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">Step 6: Calculate & Analyze</h3>
                <p>Hit "Calculate Returns" to see your total profit/loss, return percentage, CAGR, and comparison vs S&P 500 and Nifty 50.</p>
