            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <section id="faq" class="article-section">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-question"></i> Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">1. Is this calculator accurate?</h3>
                <p>Yes. We use real historical price data from Yahoo Finance and other reliable sources. Dividends are based on actual dividend payment dates and amounts. Currency conversions use historical USD-INR rates from Reserve Bank of India data.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">2. Can I calculate returns for fractional shares?</h3>
                <p>Yes. The calculator automatically handles fractional shares. If you invested ₹10,000 in Apple and the price was $150, it calculates 66.67 shares (or whatever the exact fractional amount is based on USD conversion).</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">3. Does it account for stock splits?</h3>
                <p>Yes. All prices are split-adjusted. For example, Tesla's 3-for-1 split in 2022 and Nvidia's 10-for-1 split in 2024 are already factored into historical prices.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">4. What about taxes?</h3>
                <p>The calculator shows <strong>gross returns</strong> (before taxes). Indian investors pay 20% LTCG (>24 months) + 4% cess on US stock gains. US investors pay 15-20% long-term capital gains tax. Subtract your tax rate from the final profit to get after-tax returns.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">5. Can I calculate future returns?</h3>
                <p>The calculator is primarily for historical returns. However, you can manually model future scenarios by extending the sell date and assuming price targets (e.g., "What if Nvidia reaches $1,200 by 2027?"). Use bull/base/bear case growth rates to project.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">6. Why isn't Google (Alphabet) included?</h3>
                <p>Google is a Bro Billionaire stock, but we limited the tool to the core Magnificent Seven with the highest retail following and billionaire concentration. You can use a generic stock calculator for GOOGL.</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">7. How often is data updated?</h3>
                <p>Price data is updated daily. If you select "current date" as the sell date, you'll get today's closing price (or yesterday's if markets are closed).</p>

                <h3 class="subsection-title">8. Can I use this for portfolio calculations?</h3>
                <p>Yes, but you'll need to calculate each stock individually and sum the results. For example, if you have ₹1 lakh in Nvidia and ₹50k in Tesla, run the calculator twice and add the total values.</p>
            </section>

            <div class="section-divider"></div>

